Business Problem Summary

The objective is to determine whether the new onboarding campaign should be launched, rejected, tested further, or rolled out only to selected customer segments.
The decision affects business leaders, marketing, product teams, and customers.
The main success metric is the paid conversion rate, while improvements in trial starts, onboarding completion, revenue, and engagement are also desirable.
Potential risks include increased refund requests, more support tickets, lower-quality revenue, and reduced engagement. These guardrail metrics must not worsen.
The recommendation should only be made after analyzing the experimental results and confirming that any improvements are statistically significant and provide clear business value.
